ZEQ2-Lite
Open-sourced and mod expandable project based on a highly modified ioQuake3 engine foundation and features many true-to-reference DBZ visuals and mechanics. Developer sandbox for people who want to tinker with basic game development.

281  int delta;
282  int step;
283 
284  if ( clientNum != cg.predictedPlayerState.clientNum ) {
285  break;
286  }

290  break;
291  }
292  // check for stepping up before a previous step is completed
293  delta = cg.time - cg.stepTime;
294  if (delta < STEP_TIME) {
295  oldStep = cg.stepChange * (STEP_TIME - delta) / STEP_TIME;
296  } else {
297  oldStep = 0;
298  }
299 
300  // add this amount
301  step = 4 * (event - EV_STEP_4 + 1 );
302  cg.stepChange = oldStep + step;
303  if ( cg.stepChange > MAX_STEP_CHANGE ) {
304  cg.stepChange = MAX_STEP_CHANGE;
305  }
